real_commentary: Here we go! Who will be meeting Spain in Sunday's final? The second semi-final is under way.
our_sequence_commentary: [Kick Off] The first half begins. Euro 2024 Semi-Final between Netherlands and England!

real_commentary: The Netherlands win a free-kick inside the opening 20 seconds. A long ball forward and Donyell Malen is trying to reach it but he's offside.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Declan Rice (England) on Donyell Malen (Netherlands). Free kick awarded.

real_commentary: Jude Bellingham is tussling for the ball with Xavi Simons in the centre circle. Tonight could be a good battle between the two 21-year-olds. It's a slow and steady start from both sides.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Jerdy Schouten (Netherlands) on Phil Foden (England) in midfield.

real_commentary: Nice move by England involving Jude Bellingham and Harry Kane before the ball is played out wide to Bukayo Saka who sends in a cross which is headed away.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Nathan Aké (Netherlands) on Marc Guehi (England). Free kick awarded on the right wing.

real_commentary: Great work by Bukayo Saka to steal the ball off Cody Gakpo out wide on the halfway line but England cannot make it count.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Virgil van Dijk (Netherlands) on Harry Kane (England). Free kick for England.

real_commentary: That's a rocket! No wonder they are saying good things about Xavi Simons. He wins the ball off Declan Rice and from the edge of the box unleashes an unstoppable finish into the net. Jordan Pickford dives in an attempt to keep it out but he wasn't getting to that.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Virgil van Dijk (Netherlands) on Harry Kane (England). Free kick for England.

real_commentary: Time for cool heads. England been behind before at this tournament but they have serious work to do.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Jerdy Schouten (Netherlands) on Jude Bellingham (England) near the box.

real_commentary: Bukayo Saka wins a free-kick inside the Dutch half after being shoved to the floor by Cody Gakpo. By the way, Saka has been one of England's better players so far.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Cody Mathès Gakpo (Netherlands) on Bukayo Saka (England). Free kick awarded.

real_commentary: That goal was timed at 6:41. The Netherlands have avoided defeat in their last four matches when scoring first in the European Championship, since a 2-1 loss to Portugal in 2012.
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Saved] Attempt saved. Harry Kane's right footed shot from the edge of the box denied by Bart Verbruggen.

real_commentary: SO CLOSE! Good work by Bukayo Saka leads to an attempt by Harry Kane which flashes agonisingly over. Kane is hurt after connecting with Denzel Dumfries while getting his shot away.
our_sequence_commentary: [Yellow Card] Denzel Dumfries (Netherlands) receives a yellow card for a foul on Harry Kane (England).

real_commentary: As cool as you like! He's been criticised, he's been told he's not playing well enough...but Harry Kane has got England back on level terms. Great penalty.
our_sequence_commentary: [Goal] Goal! Netherlands 0, England 1. Harry Kane scores with a right-footed shot from the centre of the box.

real_commentary: Danny Murphy has just said that penalty wouldn't have been awarded in the Premier League. Who cares?

real_commentary: Harry Kane is now joint leading scorer at Euro 2024 with three goals. Drop him? You're having a laugh.

real_commentary: England have scored each of their 13 penalties since the 2022 World Cup.

real_commentary: THIS IS SO MUCH BETTER. England fans have waited a long time for this type of performance. England are going for it and they look dangerous with every attack.

real_commentary: THIS IS SO MUCH BETTER. England fans have waited a long time for this type of performance. England are going for it and they look dangerous with every attack.

our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Blocked] Attempt blocked. Donyell Malen's left footed shot from the center of the box denied by Marc Guehi.

real_commentary: This is a brilliant watch. Two goals, a clearance off the line, a header against the bar and a long-range attempt that comes back off the post.

real_commentary: What's this? A huge blow for the Netherlands as Memphis Depay is forced off with an injury. On comes Joey Veerman.

real_commentary: They're outnumbered but they're making all the noise. It's fair to say England's fans are encouraged by what they are seeing.

real_commentary: Where has this half gone? It's flown by. Two teams who are really going for it. Two teams who really want to play Spain in Sunday's final.

real_commentary: Cheeky by Kobbie Mainoo! A back-heel from the 19-year-old for Phil Foden who goes for goal. Bart Verbruggen makes the save. Where have England been hiding? They seriously look in the mood tonight.

real_commentary: Phil Foden is playing like an animal that has been freed into the wild after being caged for so long.

our_sequence_commentary: [General] Even midfield battle continues, England slightly edging possession as Nathan Aké leads with six events.

real_commentary: I don't think England want this half to end. The reaction to falling behind has been excellent. Gareth Southgate will feel his side should really be leading.

real_commentary: England's best 45 minutes of Euro 2024. No doubt about it.

real_commentary: It's very stop-start in the early stages of the second half. There's more excitement in the stands than on the pitch. England fans have not stopped singing all match.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Bukayo Saka (England) on Virgil van Dijk (Netherlands) in the defensive half.

real_commentary: Declan Rice escapes a yellow card after a clear foul. This is highly competitive but there has only been one booking so far to Denzel Dumfries.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] England asserting dominance with 100% possession, controlling midfield play.

real_commentary: A crucial stage of this semi-final. Both teams look scared to make a mistake. This isn't being played at anywhere near the same tempo as the first half. That can all change in a flash, of course.

real_commentary: We've reached the hour mark. Too early to start talking about extra-time?

real_commentary: What has happened to this game? It was action-packed, edge of your seat stuff in the first 45 minutes. Nothing like that this half.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Phil Foden (England) on Jerdy Schouten (Netherlands) in defensive half.

real_commentary: Jordan Pickford to the rescue! A set-piece for the Dutch and it's curled into the England box and Virgil van Dijk times his run to perfection. The Netherlands captain makes a good connection and it's heading for the back of the net before Pickford flings himself to keep it out.
our_sequence_commentary: [Shots] Pressure from the Netherlands, two attempts in quick succession. Van Dijk's shot saved, Dumfries heads off target.

real_commentary: Wout Weghorst has made a couple of naughty challenges since coming on. Bukayo Saka and Phil Foden are not seeing the ball as much as they did in the first half.

real_commentary: The Dutch are whipping in cross after cross into the England box. Jordan Pickford has to stretch to put the latest one out for a corner. England have not been able to get going at all this half.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Netherlands dominating midfield with 100% possession, led by Jerdy Schouten's involvement.

real_commentary: Twenty minutes from extra-time. Still just the one change by Gareth Southgate.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Denzel Dumfries (Netherlands) on John Stones (England) in midfield.

real_commentary: It's all a bit flat as far as England are concerned. They were exciting, entertaining and threatening in the first half. Nothing like that this half.
